last week , libya 's parliament gave its conditional approval for a trial in the netherlands by a scottish court , but said some obstacles remained. the remark was made without elaboration at a news conference in algiers hours before his arrival in tunis , his final scheduled stop on a tour aimed at unblocking plans for a u.n. referendum on the disputed western sahara. al-zuwiy , the justice minister , said the two suspects will have the right to an appeal in the same court if it finds them guilty. annan spoke to reporters in tripoli after the meeting